09:36.767 --> 09:39.000
- Poet, what's up?

09:39.066 --> 09:42.266
- It's my new
work assignment,

09:42.333 --> 09:45.700
here in the morgue.

09:45.767 --> 09:50.133
McManus' revenge on me
for screwing up outside, man.

09:50.200 --> 09:52.000
- Yeah, what
happened, man?

09:52.066 --> 09:53.367
You was free.

09:53.433 --> 09:55.567
- Yeah,
and still a fiend.

09:55.633 --> 09:59.734
I spent all the money I got
for that book on crack,

09:59.800 --> 10:02.233
and when the cash ran out,

10:02.300 --> 10:03.800
them fucking dealers
came after me, man.

10:03.867 --> 10:06.033
I was defending myself.

10:07.500 --> 10:10.367
- [scoffs]
You shot a guy six times.

10:10.433 --> 10:12.500
- I had to make sure
the nigga was dead.

10:12.567 --> 10:14.266
- Yeah.

10:14.333 --> 10:16.467
- So what do
we do here?

10:16.533 --> 10:18.100
- You know,
wait for the mortician

10:18.166 --> 10:19.467
to get back from lunch.

10:19.533 --> 10:21.934
Undertaker school in town
sends a student up to work

10:22.000 --> 10:24.033
on our corpses
for the practice.

10:24.100 --> 10:25.467
- We help them out?

10:25.533 --> 10:27.000
- Yeah, you know,
hand them shit--

10:27.066 --> 10:30.133
embalming fluid,
cosmetics...

10:30.200 --> 10:31.734
- Cosmetics?

10:31.800 --> 10:34.500
You mean like--
you mean like lipstick and shit?

10:34.567 --> 10:37.767
- Sure. You got to look pretty
before they plant you.

10:39.734 --> 10:41.967
- Shit, I ain't no girl.

10:42.033 --> 10:44.000
They ain't putting none
of that shit on my face, yo.

10:44.066 --> 10:47.266
- When you're dead you
don't have much of a choice.

10:47.333 --> 10:50.333
Death is a lot
like life in Oz, man.

10:52.567 --> 10:55.100
It'll work.
I'm telling you, it'll work.

10:55.166 --> 10:56.767
- What are you talking about?
What'll work?

10:56.834 --> 10:59.000
- Yo, check this out.

10:59.066 --> 11:01.433
Money got a plan
to escape out of Oz, yo.

11:01.500 --> 11:03.433
- What's up?
What's up?

11:03.500 --> 11:05.934
- Yo, we working
stiff patrol, right?

11:06.000 --> 11:06.934
- Right.

11:07.000 --> 11:08.300
- So just now we loaded

11:08.367 --> 11:10.300
those two Aryan fucks
into boxes, right,

11:10.367 --> 11:12.433
which get sent to
a funeral home for burial.

11:12.500 --> 11:15.867
So my idea is,
next time somebody dies,

11:15.934 --> 11:18.367
I get in the box instead.

11:18.433 --> 11:19.633
- Hill...

11:19.700 --> 11:21.166
coffins are air-tight.

11:21.233 --> 11:22.667
You'd die of asphyxiation.
- Thank you.

11:22.734 --> 11:24.734
- Not if I drill some subtle
little holes

11:24.800 --> 11:25.867
in the right places.

11:25.934 --> 11:27.100
- Yeah, but the casket
would be sealed.

11:27.166 --> 11:28.433
You'd be trapped inside.

11:28.500 --> 11:30.066
- Not if I get a couple
of friends of mine

11:30.133 --> 11:32.066
to come to the funeral home
and break me out.

11:32.133 --> 11:33.333
- Yeah, but what you gonna do

11:33.400 --> 11:34.900
with the real motherfuckers
that die?

11:34.967 --> 11:36.500
- Mm-hmm.

11:36.567 --> 11:38.734
- How hard is it to hide a
couple of bodies up in Oz, son?

11:38.800 --> 11:41.100
Temporarily at least?

11:41.166 --> 11:42.767
- It's a good plan.
- Good plan.

11:42.834 --> 11:43.934
Shit might work.

11:44.000 --> 11:45.433
- That's what
I'm saying.

11:45.500 --> 11:48.100
- That's better than having
a motherfucker mail you out.

11:48.166 --> 11:49.300
- No, man, I was bullshitting.

11:49.367 --> 11:50.934
- I wouldn't be telling
everybody.

11:51.000 --> 11:53.800
- But I was bullshitting.
You thought I wanted--

11:53.867 --> 11:55.967
Express mail.
- Yeah, all right.

11:56.033 --> 11:58.667
- Every inmate
wants out of prison,

11:58.734 --> 12:00.633
by hook or by crook.

12:00.700 --> 12:03.033
Of course, there are some
who find that once they're free,

12:03.100 --> 12:06.100
life on the other side ain't
all it's cracked up to be.

12:06.166 --> 12:10.266
[thunder booming]

12:10.333 --> 12:12.467
- I'm here to see
Sister Peter Marie.

12:12.533 --> 12:16.900
[indistinct chatter]

12:16.967 --> 12:20.233
- Robert Sippel's
out front asking for you.

12:22.767 --> 12:25.066
So, Father, meet any cute boys
on the outside?

12:25.133 --> 12:27.767
Any boys
with the first name Dick?

12:27.834 --> 12:30.333
[chuckles]

12:34.033 --> 12:36.066
- You look exhausted.

12:36.133 --> 12:38.066
- Well, the last few days
have been very difficult.

12:38.133 --> 12:40.834
Registering
as a convicted pervert

12:40.900 --> 12:43.300
was more difficult
than I thought.

12:43.367 --> 12:44.834
I had to go down
to the courthouse

12:44.900 --> 12:47.166
and stand in line
with ordinary people...

12:49.000 --> 12:52.367
Wanting fishing licenses
and learner's permits.

12:53.533 --> 12:55.533
I stepped up
to the counter

12:55.600 --> 12:58.033
and softly explained
to the clerk why I was there.

12:58.100 --> 12:59.233
She boomed,

12:59.300 --> 13:01.200
"Perverts
fill out these."

13:01.266 --> 13:02.600
- Oh, boy.

13:02.667 --> 13:05.266
So, uh...

13:05.333 --> 13:06.934
how's the
job search going?

13:07.000 --> 13:11.266
- [scoffs] Seek and ye
shall find, right?

13:11.333 --> 13:13.400
It's hard enough getting
employment as an ex-con,

13:13.467 --> 13:16.934
but once they discover that
I've fondled a young boy...

13:17.000 --> 13:19.467
- Well, have you found
a place to live?

13:19.533 --> 13:21.400
- After ten years
of imprisonment,

13:21.467 --> 13:23.767
my first two nights
of freedom

13:23.834 --> 13:26.066
were spent sleeping
on the subway.

13:26.133 --> 13:27.467
- [sighs]

13:27.533 --> 13:30.033
Well, you know I'll do
anything I can to help.

13:30.100 --> 13:32.700
- Well, that's
why I'm here.

13:32.767 --> 13:35.433
Would you please speak
with Warden Glynn?

13:35.500 --> 13:37.333
- About what?

13:38.300 --> 13:40.667
- Letting me sleep
here in Oz.

13:40.734 --> 13:43.767
- You want me to let
Robert Sippel move into a cell?

13:43.834 --> 13:46.033
- Just until he finds a
landlord who'll rent him a room.

13:46.100 --> 13:48.200
- [sighs] I need to see
the shift log.

13:48.266 --> 13:50.967
He'll have to
stay in Gen Pop.

13:51.033 --> 13:53.000
He'll be at risk.

13:53.066 --> 13:54.200
- Yeah, he's
aware of that.

13:54.266 --> 13:55.767
- You know, he's not
gonna get an apartment

13:55.834 --> 13:56.800
unless he has a job.

13:56.867 --> 13:58.834
- Well, that's my
next mission.

13:58.900 --> 14:00.433
I got to find somebody who
will hire a defrocked priest.

14:00.500 --> 14:02.300
- I will.

14:02.367 --> 14:03.433
- You?

14:03.500 --> 14:05.600
- Yeah, as my assistant.

14:05.667 --> 14:08.333
I've got a discretionary fund
from the diocese.

14:08.400 --> 14:11.433
I guess it's time
I used my discretion.

14:13.100 --> 14:15.433
Well, there's not
much room here, but...

14:15.500 --> 14:17.166
- I appreciate
this, Father.

14:17.233 --> 14:20.533
- Oh, yeah, well,
I needed a--

14:20.600 --> 14:23.767
As you can see,
I'm not very organized.

14:23.834 --> 14:26.066
- You're still
uncomfortable around me.

14:29.533 --> 14:30.900
[phone ringing]

14:30.967 --> 14:34.100
Chaplin's office.

14:34.166 --> 14:35.333
Yes.

14:36.400 --> 14:40.834
Okay, okay,
I'll tell him.

14:40.900 --> 14:43.233
A patient in the
hospital is dying.

14:43.300 --> 14:45.000
He's asked
for the anointing.

14:49.300 --> 14:52.066
If I'm really here
to help you, Father,

14:52.133 --> 14:53.667
let me help you.

15:01.066 --> 15:03.133
- He pardons
all your inequities.

15:03.200 --> 15:04.700
He heals all your ills.

15:04.767 --> 15:06.567
He redeems your
life from destruction.

15:06.633 --> 15:09.800
He crowns you with His
kindness and compassion.

15:09.867 --> 15:12.000
Father in Heaven,
through this holy anointing,

15:12.066 --> 15:14.734
grant Joseph comfort
in his suffering.

15:14.800 --> 15:17.867
Through Christ
our lord, amen.

15:17.934 --> 15:21.367
[gate buzzes]

15:21.433 --> 15:22.900
Mr. Hannssel.

15:22.967 --> 15:24.300
Hi, I'm Father Mukada.

15:24.367 --> 15:25.700
- Thanks for
seeing me.

15:25.767 --> 15:26.967
- Sure.

15:27.033 --> 15:28.200
- This past few weeks,

15:28.266 --> 15:29.567
there's been plenty of stuff
in the press,

15:29.633 --> 15:31.767
what, with the legislature
passing that law requiring

15:31.834 --> 15:35.333
sex offenders to register
and Father Sippel getting out.

15:35.400 --> 15:37.967
It stirred up
a lot of things in me--

15:38.033 --> 15:40.066
feelings I thought
I'd put down.

15:40.133 --> 15:43.467
- I told him that
you were coming.

15:43.533 --> 15:46.300
- Is he willing to
talk with me?

15:46.367 --> 15:47.900
- Yes.

15:47.967 --> 15:51.967
He feels that he owes
you that much, at least.

15:52.033 --> 15:54.467
- I've never been
in prison before.

15:54.533 --> 15:56.000
- Don't worry.

15:56.066 --> 15:58.133
There'll be a correctional
officer with you the whole time.

15:58.200 --> 16:00.633
- Yeah,
to protect me...

16:00.700 --> 16:02.166
or him?

16:03.800 --> 16:05.667
[chuckles]
I'm sorry, Father.

16:05.734 --> 16:08.400
Look, I have no intention
of harming the man.

16:08.467 --> 16:12.800
I don't really know what
my intentions are except, uh...

16:14.400 --> 16:18.200
I haven't seen
him since that day.

16:18.266 --> 16:21.467
Ten years is a long time
to carry the shit inside.

16:21.533 --> 16:25.066
Sorry to say "shit"
in front of a priest.

16:26.633 --> 16:29.500
- Sometimes "shit" is
the only word that fits.

16:36.266 --> 16:43.333
♪ ♪

17:08.000 --> 17:09.934
- Yes?

17:10.000 --> 17:12.467
- How do you live
with yourself?

17:12.533 --> 17:13.934
- How do you?

17:14.000 --> 17:15.400
- [scoffs]

17:15.467 --> 17:18.900
Whatever I've done,
I've done for righteous reasons.

17:20.700 --> 17:25.734
