57:44.300 --> 57:47.867
I thought to myself, "Hey...

57:47.934 --> 57:49.567
this is the will of Allah."

57:49.633 --> 57:52.834
I can go to Oz,
and I can help my brothers.

57:52.900 --> 57:54.500
- And you haven't.

57:54.567 --> 57:57.500
I feel the same way
sometimes.

57:57.567 --> 57:59.767
Oh, I know you do,
McManus.

57:59.834 --> 58:01.767
I see you.

58:01.834 --> 58:05.000
The difference is you can
go home every night.

58:05.066 --> 58:08.400
You're free to quit,
get yourself another job.

58:09.633 --> 58:13.834
I'm gonna be here
for another 17 years.

58:13.900 --> 58:16.000
I've been thinking
a lot lately

58:16.066 --> 58:18.567
about what else I could've done
with that time.

58:18.633 --> 58:20.533
- You mean like
have a family?

58:20.600 --> 58:22.600
- Oh, yes.

58:22.667 --> 58:25.233
- You still can
when you get out.

58:25.300 --> 58:26.734
You're not too old.

58:26.800 --> 58:29.066
- After two decades
in maximum security,

58:29.133 --> 58:31.633
what the hell would I have
to offer a wife?

58:31.700 --> 58:34.600
What could I
offer a child?

58:34.667 --> 58:36.133
- Your faith.

58:36.200 --> 58:39.433
I thought your faith
sustained you.

58:41.700 --> 58:44.100
- It does...

58:45.800 --> 58:48.433
Most of the time.

58:48.500 --> 58:52.266
[door rumbles open]

58:52.333 --> 58:54.900
- Attention--
the following prisoners

58:54.967 --> 58:57.100
are to report
to the warden's office,

58:57.166 --> 59:00.700
97F444, Kareem Said,

59:00.767 --> 59:05.066
97A622, Zahir Arif,

59:05.133 --> 59:08.433
89B267, Nasim Bismilla,

59:08.500 --> 59:12.100
85A245, Sanjay Afsana.

59:13.834 --> 59:15.500
- Said.

59:17.600 --> 59:19.200
Have a seat.

59:21.433 --> 59:23.567
- Said,

59:23.633 --> 59:25.834
every year the governor
grants clemency

59:25.900 --> 59:27.500
for a number
of prisoners.

59:27.567 --> 59:29.000
- Just around
Christmastime.

59:29.066 --> 59:31.300
- This year he's decided to do
two special releases--

59:31.367 --> 59:33.433
one for Passover,
one for Ramadan.

59:33.500 --> 59:34.767
- I know
all about this.

59:34.834 --> 59:36.467
I've been working
with other Islamic leaders

59:36.533 --> 59:38.400
trying to get
the government to initiate it.

59:38.467 --> 59:39.767
- Right.

59:39.834 --> 59:41.633
Devlin's asked us
to go over the case files

59:41.700 --> 59:44.200
of our Muslim prisoners
and recommend a candidate.

59:44.266 --> 59:47.233
- But he specifically
wanted us to consider you.

59:50.934 --> 59:52.700
- It's a trick, right?

59:52.767 --> 59:55.667
There has to be
strings attached.

59:57.266 --> 59:59.867
Exactly what do I have to
give up to gain my freedom?

59:59.934 --> 1:00:01.100
- Nothing.

1:00:01.166 --> 1:00:03.333
- The big question is,

1:00:03.400 --> 1:00:05.900
if the governor
offers clemency,

1:00:05.967 --> 1:00:08.200
will you take it?

1:00:14.133 --> 1:00:16.567
- Yes.

1:00:16.633 --> 1:00:18.734
[bell ringing]

1:00:18.800 --> 1:00:20.200
I tell you this--

1:00:20.266 --> 1:00:22.567
we must be happy for
whichever one of us is chosen.

1:00:22.633 --> 1:00:25.200
- Yeah, especially
if it's you.

1:00:26.533 --> 1:00:28.033
- Arif?

1:00:28.100 --> 1:00:29.867
- I'm sorry.

1:00:29.934 --> 1:00:31.767
It's just that
I have children.

1:00:31.834 --> 1:00:35.967
I know they're being careful,
but it's not the same thing.

1:00:36.033 --> 1:00:40.100
They miss me.
I miss them.

1:00:40.166 --> 1:00:41.934
- I know.

1:00:42.000 --> 1:00:45.300
- Do you?

1:00:45.367 --> 1:00:48.300
[tense percussive tones]

1:00:48.367 --> 1:00:55.300
♪ ♪

1:00:55.367 --> 1:00:58.400
- [sighs]

1:01:11.600 --> 1:01:13.900
- It's all about Said.
- That's the will of Allah.

1:01:13.967 --> 1:01:15.467
- Come on, now.

1:01:15.533 --> 1:01:18.333
- Stop it! Stop it!

1:01:18.400 --> 1:01:20.767
- Hey, hey,
what's going on?

1:01:20.834 --> 1:01:23.100
Step away.

1:01:23.166 --> 1:01:24.533
- Madness.

1:01:26.066 --> 1:01:27.900
- Come here.
Come here.

1:01:27.967 --> 1:01:31.000
[gate buzzes]

1:01:33.700 --> 1:01:35.100
You're the one,

1:01:35.166 --> 1:01:37.700
the one
Devlin's chosen.

1:01:41.800 --> 1:01:44.533
- [chuckles]

1:01:47.200 --> 1:01:49.900
- Ramadan
starts Thursday.

1:01:49.967 --> 1:01:54.400
He's doing
a press conference.

1:01:54.467 --> 1:01:55.934
I...

1:01:57.467 --> 1:01:59.834
I feel like I should
congratulate you, but...

1:01:59.900 --> 1:02:01.533
- But what?

1:02:01.600 --> 1:02:04.166
Don't tell me you're gonna
miss me when I'm gone.

1:02:04.233 --> 1:02:05.900
- No, not at all.

1:02:05.967 --> 1:02:08.233
It's just...

1:02:08.300 --> 1:02:11.266
none of this
sits right with me.

1:02:14.467 --> 1:02:16.100
As-salaam alaikum.

1:02:16.166 --> 1:02:19.133
[tense percussive tones]

1:02:19.200 --> 1:02:23.767
♪ ♪

1:02:23.834 --> 1:02:26.000
- And the celebration
of Ramadan

1:02:26.066 --> 1:02:28.300
is at the center
of Islamic worship,

1:02:28.367 --> 1:02:30.567
therefore, I'm pleased,

1:02:30.633 --> 1:02:33.200
in the grand tradition
of this holy time,

1:02:33.266 --> 1:02:37.567
to bestow clemency
on a prisoner.

1:02:37.633 --> 1:02:41.834
Kareem Said has been
an outspoken critic

1:02:41.900 --> 1:02:43.400
of our administration,

1:02:43.467 --> 1:02:44.734
but political
differences aside,

1:02:44.800 --> 1:02:46.734
he has been
an outstanding member

1:02:46.800 --> 1:02:48.734
of the prison
population.

1:02:48.800 --> 1:02:50.900
Even after suffering
a heart attack last year,

1:02:51.000 --> 1:02:53.100
he's continued to work
with prisoners

1:02:53.166 --> 1:02:54.934
of every race and color,
especially the young,

1:02:55.000 --> 1:02:59.266
to instruct them and
to guide them to better lives.

1:02:59.333 --> 1:03:03.633
So, I hereby grant
Kareem Said

1:03:03.700 --> 1:03:06.333
a full pardon,

1:03:06.400 --> 1:03:11.200
and I wish him well
in his new life.

1:03:11.266 --> 1:03:13.200
[applause]

1:03:13.266 --> 1:03:16.367
[reporters shouting]

1:03:19.934 --> 1:03:23.100
- Finally we meet
face-to-face.

1:03:23.166 --> 1:03:25.900
- Mr. Said,
how do you feel?

1:03:25.967 --> 1:03:27.533
- How do I feel?

1:03:27.600 --> 1:03:30.433
[scoffs]

1:03:30.500 --> 1:03:33.367
I feel joyless.

1:03:33.433 --> 1:03:36.333
My brothers
remain behind,

1:03:36.400 --> 1:03:39.967
imprisoned, suppressed.

1:03:40.033 --> 1:03:42.967
I don't just mean
my Muslim brothers.

1:03:43.033 --> 1:03:46.066
I mean every single man that
will sleep in here tonight,

1:03:46.133 --> 1:03:48.800
that was cut off
from everything that he loves,

1:03:48.867 --> 1:03:52.900
cut off
from his own self.

1:03:52.967 --> 1:03:55.533
You know,
as the word went around

1:03:55.600 --> 1:03:58.433
that the governor was gonna
give somebody clemency...

1:03:59.834 --> 1:04:02.867
I saw a riff develop

1:04:02.934 --> 1:04:06.367
as each inmate wished himself
to be the chosen one.

1:04:08.400 --> 1:04:10.934
The longing to be free
became as palpable

1:04:11.000 --> 1:04:12.533
as the food that we eat.

1:04:12.600 --> 1:04:14.367
[scoffs]

1:04:14.433 --> 1:04:19.166
But it is a meal that I am
being served right now...

1:04:20.700 --> 1:04:23.834
And I am Muslim,

1:04:23.900 --> 1:04:28.467
and Allah does not allow me
to swallow certain things.

1:04:28.533 --> 1:04:31.033
Allah does not allow me
to take scraps

1:04:31.100 --> 1:04:33.900
from the hands of a man
such as this...

1:04:33.967 --> 1:04:38.467
a man who is
corrupt and immoral,

1:04:38.533 --> 1:04:41.400
a man who denigrates
the gift of clemency

1:04:41.467 --> 1:04:43.900
just as he violates
the principles of justice,

1:04:43.967 --> 1:04:45.500
a man that
gave the order

1:04:45.567 --> 1:04:48.667
that caused the death
of eight people.

1:04:48.734 --> 1:04:50.700
And so, Governor Devlin,

1:04:50.767 --> 1:04:54.800
because even the cost
of freedom can be too high,

1:04:54.867 --> 1:04:56.967
I refuse your pardon.

1:04:57.033 --> 1:05:00.367
[all yelling]

1:05:02.300 --> 1:05:04.667
Officer,
take him back inside.

1:05:04.734 --> 1:05:06.600
[reporters shouting]

1:05:06.667 --> 1:05:07.600
- Cocksucker.

1:05:07.667 --> 1:05:10.133
[all clamoring]

1:05:10.200 --> 1:05:12.867
[shouting continues]

1:05:12.934 --> 1:05:17.066
[clamoring continues]

1:05:19.200 --> 1:05:20.567
- Stupid!

1:05:20.633 --> 1:05:23.400
[shouting continues]

1:05:25.433 --> 1:05:27.967
- How do you respond
to this, Governor?

1:05:29.533 --> 1:05:31.600
[gate buzzes]

1:05:31.667 --> 1:05:33.900
[prisoners cheering]

1:05:40.467 --> 1:05:44.100
[prisoners chanting]
Said, Said, Said, Said,

1:05:44.166 --> 1:05:47.900
Said, Said, Said, Said,

1:05:47.967 --> 1:05:50.467
Said, Said, Said,

1:05:50.533 --> 1:05:54.567
Said, Said, Said, Said,

1:05:54.633 --> 1:05:57.900
Said, Said, Said, Said,

1:05:57.967 --> 1:06:02.400
Said, Said, Said, Said,

1:06:02.467 --> 1:06:06.734
Said, Said, Said, Said,

1:06:06.800 --> 1:06:10.600
Said, Said, Said, Said!

1:06:10.667 --> 1:06:12.467
- Yeah...

1:06:12.533 --> 1:06:16.800
everybody wants
to escape from Oz.

1:06:16.867 --> 1:06:19.233
Of course, the truth is,

1:06:19.300 --> 1:06:21.600
there is no escape.

1:06:21.667 --> 1:06:24.233
I mean, let's say
you manage to sneak out,

1:06:24.300 --> 1:06:27.900
then you got to run
and keep running.

1:06:27.967 --> 1:06:32.200
A life of running away
ain't no life at all.

1:06:32.266 --> 1:06:34.166
Better to stay put,
face reality,

1:06:34.233 --> 1:06:37.033
deal with what you've got,
and make the best of it.

1:06:37.100 --> 1:06:38.700
Yeah.

1:06:38.767 --> 1:06:41.867
The measure of a man
is not where he lives,

1:06:41.934 --> 1:06:45.400
but how,
how he makes the best of it.

1:06:45.467 --> 1:06:48.300
Make the best of it.

1:06:49.967 --> 1:06:52.066
Later.

1:06:53.300 --> 1:06:56.233
[tense percussive tones]

1:06:56.300 --> 1:07:03.333
♪ ♪
